# default.always-allow — shipped defaults for the always-allow hook.
#
# Flat list of POSIX ERE patterns. A Bash command is auto-allowed (the
# permission prompt is suppressed) if it matches any entry. Multi-command
# lines (containing &&, ||, ;, |, or newlines) and background commands are
# never auto-allowed regardless of these rules.
#
# Loaded together with $HOME/.claude/.always-allow and
# $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/.always-allow — all three files concatenate. To remove
# a default rule, comment out the line here; there is no `!` negation.
#
# Comments begin with # and run to end of line.
#
# This file ships with the always-allow hook. Keep it free of
# project-specific patterns — those belong in $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/.always-allow.
